Hello all. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br />Firstly, I would like to say that english is not my natural language. So, sorry my future mistakes. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br />I'm purchasing a copy of an original japanese Final Fantasy 3 60pins, and, with it in hands, I will try burn an eprom with the translated ROM <strong>for my own use</strong>.<br /><br />I've noticed there is no CHR ROM, only a 512KiB PRG ROM (32 x 16KiB).<br /><br />I was wondering two things:<br /><br />1 - The only eprom I will need to burn is that PRG? The others 2 (of 3) chips on the original board doesn't need to be removed?<br /><br />2 - Anyone knows about REWIRING on this board? I will probably need to do this, right? On Nesdev I just found how to rewiring "TKROM -&gt; TNROM conversion (mapper 4)". I know that FF3 uses TNROM, it's the right conversion?<br /><br /><br />I will put the PCB scan here too: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/image.php?ImageID=3830">http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/image.php?ImageID=3830</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Thank you very much.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3432">Harry Hardon</a> — Sun Nov 11, 2007 1:52 pm</p><hr />
